citations:
    citation-agot-eddard-v:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Eddard V"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "The Hand's tourney (called 'the king's tourney'). Janos Slynt commands the City Watch and complains of crime. Sandor Clegane vs Jaime Lannister — Sandor wins second pass, knocks Jaime from his horse. Ser Gregor Clegane vs Ser Loras Tyrell — Loras uses a mare in heat to unseat Gregor; Gregor kills his horse and attacks Loras; Sandor intervenes to save Loras; Robert halts the fight. Loras yields champion's purse to Sandor. Thoros of Myr wins the melee with a flaming sword. Ser Hugh of the Vale (knight killed in tourney) is identified by Varys as the likely poisoner of Jon Arryn. Varys reveals Jon Arryn was poisoned with 'the tears of Lys.' Varys warns of Lannister plot to kill Robert during the melee. Ned discovers Robert has bastard children: Gendry (armorer's apprentice), a girl in the Vale, and a boy at Storm's End."
